cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.ST, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new objective function for training deep neural network based density ratio estimators and applies it to a change point detection problem. This work involves machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, and statistical analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also applies the proposed method to image data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and change point detection, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.ST (Statistics).
